                    <h2>
                        Adopt A Plant Campaign - ADAPT</h2>
                    <br />
                    <div class="border_image">
                        <p>
                            Our green initiative- Adopt A Plant (ADAPT) plants saplings across all campuses
                            with LFT Clubs once a year.</p>
                        <p>
                            This campaign is usually conducted in the month of September by each college unit.
                            As a part of the campaign the students motivate their peers to join them in planting
                            and adopting a plant. These students come together to plant saplings in over 100
                            locations in and around their colleges.</p>
                        <p>
                            A total of 8000 saplings have been planted and adopted by the LFT members from various
                            college clubs who pledged to plant and nurture the saplings in their years on campus.</p>
                        <a href="#">Album</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div align="center">
                    <h2>
                        Anti Drugs and Anti Ragging Campaign - ADAR
                    </h2>
                    <br />
                    <div class="border_image">
                        <p>
                            Leaders for Tomorrow has been campaigning against substance abuse and ragging for
                            the past three years. With the partnership of Delhi Police, Leaders for Tomorrow,
                            launched ADAR – Anti Drugs and Anti Ragging Campaign 2012 in all the major colleges
                            of Delhi NCR.</p>
                        <p>
                            The mission of LFT’s battle against drugs and ragging is to tell the youth that
                            for a healthier life, they must respect themselves by staying away from drugs and
                            respect others by staying away from any activity associated with ragging.Thus the
                            campaign is titled ADAR (meaning respect in Hindi) to help the students associate
                            with the cause.</p>
                        <p>
                            This year, ADAR Campaign was bigger than ever as it was conducted in partnership
                            with the Delhi Police. The police showed immense support by helping the volunteers
                            take strict action in case of ragging and by providing valuable information on substance
                            abuse and ragging.</p>
                        <p>
                            1500 volunteers from across 150 colleges set up Help Desks and did an active signature
                            campaign in 200 colleges, thereby reaching out to nearly 5 lakh students directly
                            in our movement towards social change. The 5 day Campaign was conducted 8 universities
                            such as Delhi University GGSIP University, Private and Independent Universities
                            including Amity University, Gautam Budh University, Delhi Technological University,
                            Jaypee University etc.</p>
